            . I lodge at Darby's. About the end of April, the prisoner came and asked me for a lodging, saying, she was distressed; and referred me to No. 26, Northampton-street.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Smith agreed to take another lodging with me - I went after one, she told me to take the things to the lodging - I met my husband, and could not go.</p>
